The paper discusses performance estimation methods for time series forecasting tasks in machine learning. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper specifically addresses the challenges posed by time series data, which suggests that it could also be classified under the sub-category of statistics (cs.ST). The use of cross-validation and out-of-sample approaches also suggests that the paper could be relevant to the sub-categories of data science (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
